ISSUE.TITLE: Syntax error in python documentation for setting session data
ISSUE.DESCRIPTION: # Improve documentation ## Link https://supabase.com/docs/reference/python/auth-setsession ## Describe the problem The code snippet is missing an extra curly brace near the end: ```res = supabase.auth.set_session({"access_token": access_token, "refresh_token": refresh_token)``` The code causes this error when run: ``` res = supabase.auth.set_session({"access_token": access_token, "refresh_token": refresh_token) SyntaxError: closing parenthesis ')' does not match opening parenthesis '{' ``` ## Describe the improvement Fix the syntax so that it is formatted like this: ```res = supabase.auth.set_session({"access_token": access_token, "refresh_token": refresh_token})``` ## Additional context I will assign myself this issue and create a pull request
